We got so many questions from you guys! Thanks for your participation! 🥲 we got a lot of similar questions so we had to put some of them together and change it into a video recording. This is our first time recording a Q&A session with our Eggbun Coach, so please understand why there may be mistakes.🙏
If you have any other questions, DM us anytime! And if you enjoyed the video, please let us know, and then we will continue making more of these!
Thank you for watching and see you guys in class!👍👍

node.text:
Finally, it’s a new semester of Basic Korean class with Taeheon!😀🇰🇷
Don’t miss your chance to practice both Korean writing and speaking!
Eggbun School is an intensive 8-week Korean language course. Our students are provided with all the materials, feedback by a native speaker, biweekly 1:1 phone call lessons and more!
The new semester starts in September!

Check out the link in bio for details (the name of the class is “Basic Korean with Taeheon” )  and can’t wait to see you in class!

It’s time for a new semester of Upper-Beginner Class of Eggbun School! This class is a great option for students who finished Eggbun Basic Korean Courses, or students who think they’re on the Upper-Beginner step of their Korean journey!  This class focuses on practical, real-life Korean expressions, so you can actually use these phrases in your everyday Korean conversation.

Check the link in our bio for more details (price, curriculum)! Can’t wait to see you in class!

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'eggbun EDUCATION 정알이지_상아예살고싶요답니다 정말이지 계살고싶었답니다 친절한금자시 '너나 잘하세요' is a famous line from a movie by Park Chan-wook, Sympathy for Lady Vengeance (친절한 금자씨). This phrase can be used towards those people who can't manage their own job well, but are busy giving too much advice and telling others what to do. This phrase is a grammatically incorrect combination of 너나 (반말, casual style) and 잘하세요 (존댓말, polite style), so it can't be used towards respectful people (e.g. superiors at work, teachers, people you don't know), or otherwise, you will be considered rude.'.
